    <body>
      <entry xml:id="entry_lacamarz" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
        <form type="lemma"><orth>lacamarz</orth></form>
        <usg><lang/></usg>
        <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>неряшливый</q>
            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>naughty</q>
            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>неряха</q>
            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>a naughty person</q>
            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>грязнуля</q>
            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>a dirty person</q>
            </abv:tr></sense><sense/></sense>
        <abv:exampleGrp>
          <abv:example>
            <quote>divilduntæ, lacamarz…</quote>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>в лохмотьях, неряшливый…</q>
            </abv:tr>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>in rags, naughty…</q>
            </abv:tr>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_Iræf" type="bibl"/>
              <biblScope>46</biblScope></bibl>
          </abv:example>
        </abv:exampleGrp>
        <etym xml:lang="ru">Может быть, можно возводить к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec"
              >frasa-marza-</w></mentioned>, имея в виду для второй части <mentioned xml:lang="cu"
              ><lang/><w n="0">мръз-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
            <w>мерзить</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>мерзкий</w></mentioned>
            (<mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/>
            <w type="rec">merǵ-</w></mentioned>: <bibl><ref target="#ref_Pokorny" type="bibl"
              /><biblScope>740</biblScope></bibl>), а для первой (<mentioned xml:lang="ine"><w
              type="rec">frasa-</w></mentioned> ← <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><w type="rec"
            >parsa-</w></mentioned>) — <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
            <w>pāsa-</w> (<w type="rec">parsa</w>) <gloss><q>свинья</q></gloss></mentioned> (из
          иранского: <mentioned xml:lang="fi"><lang/>
            <w>porsas</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-mordvin"><lang/>
            <w>puŕts</w></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
            <w>prasę</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="bg" extralang="cs sr"><lang/>
            <w>prase</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
            <w>поросенок</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
            <w>parcus</w></mentioned> и пр. Звуковое развитие: <c>f-</c> перед <c>r</c> отпало, как
          обычно (ср. <ref target="#entry_lymæn" type="xr"/>, <ref target="#entry_rag" type="xr"/>,
            <ref target="#entry_rong" type="xr"/>), <c>r-</c> → <c>l</c> по диссимиляции со вторым
            <c>r</c> (как в <ref target="#entry_læmaryn" type="xr"/> и др.); <c>s</c> → <c>с</c>,
          как в <ref target="#entry_barc" type="xr"/> из <mentioned xml:lang="os"><w type="rec"
              >bars</w></mentioned>, <ref target="#entry_fæsarc" type="xr"/> из <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_fæsarc"><w type="rec">fæsarc</w></ref> и др. — Связь с <ref
            target="#entry_læx" type="xr"/>, которую предполагает <bibl><author>Gershevitch</author>
            (<ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOAS"></ref> <biblScope>1955 XVII 482</biblScope>)</bibl>, сомнительна, поскольку
          восстанавливаемое им <mentioned xml:lang="os"><w type="rec">laxša-</w></mentioned>
          нереально.</etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">May be derived from <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w type="rec"
              >frasa-marza-</w></mentioned>, keeping in mind, for the latter part, <mentioned
            xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
            <w>mrъz-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
            <w>merzitʼ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>merzkij</w></mentioned>
            (<mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/>
            <w type="rec">merǵ-</w></mentioned>: <bibl><ref target="#ref_Pokorny" type="bibl"/>
            <biblScope>740</biblScope></bibl>), and for the former (<mentioned xml:lang="ine"><w
              type="rec">frasa-</w></mentioned> ← <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><w type="rec"
            >parsa-</w></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
            <w>pāsa-</w> (<w type="rec">parsa</w>) <gloss><q>pig</q></gloss></mentioned> (from
          Iranian: <mentioned xml:lang="fi"><lang/>
            <w>porsas</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-mordvin"><lang/>
            <w>puŕts</w></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
            <w>prasę</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="bg" extralang="cs sr"><lang/>
            <w>prase</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
            <w>porosënok</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
            <w>parcus</w></mentioned> etc. Phonetic development: <c>f-</c> before <c>r</c>
          disappeared as usual (cf. <ref target="#entry_lymæn" type="xr"/>, <ref target="#entry_rag"
            type="xr"/>, <ref target="#entry_rong" type="xr"/>), <c>r-</c> → <c>l</c> due to
          dissimilation with the second <c>r</c> (as in <ref target="#entry_læmaryn" type="xr"/>
          etc.); <c>s</c> → <c>c</c>, as in <ref target="#entry_barc" type="xr"/> from <mentioned
            xml:lang="os"><w type="rec">bars</w></mentioned>, <ref target="#entry_fæsarc" type="xr"
          /> from <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæsarc"><w type="rec">fæsarc</w></ref> etc. — The
          connection with <ref target="#entry_læx" type="xr"/>, which is proposed by
              <bibl><author>Gershevitch</author> (<ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOAS"></ref> <biblScope>1955 XVII
          482</biblScope>)</bibl>, is dubious, because the word <mentioned xml:lang="os"><w
              type="rec">laxša-</w></mentioned> he reconstructs is impossible.</etym>
      </entry>
